# VibeArch Docs Rule

- Use direct, practical language with maximum annoyed OS-dev energy.
- Keep docs technically precise; snark should sharpen the message, not replace it.
- Swearing is allowed when it helps make the point.
- Every behavior change must include matching doc updates.
- Include exact commands and expected outcomes.
- Include common failure modes and recovery commands.
- Put destructive warnings before the destructive step.
